{"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkit\/external-keyboards-article"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"KeyboardKit"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"External Keyboards"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This article describes the KeyboardKit external keyboard engine."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/External-Keyboards-Article"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Connecting an external keyboard to your iPhone or iPad will cause your keyboard extension to stop working as expected.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For instance, the text document proxy will not update while you type on the external keyboard, which makes it impossible to provide features like autocomplete.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro"},{"type":"text","text":" unlocks ways to detect if an external keyboard is connected to the device, to let you adjust your keyboard accordingly."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Important about external keyboards","anchor":"Important-about-external-keyboards","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Your keyboard extension will start to behave strangely when you type on an external keyboard."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For instance, the keyboard extension will stop receiving information about when text changes. This makes it hard to provide features like autocomplete."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Using a scheduled timer to continuously check the text doesnâ€™t help, since the text document proxy will not update until you interact with the keyboard extension.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One way to force the proxy to update is to move the text cursor, but this may interfere with the typing. Imagine typing with a cursor that suddenly moves back then forward again."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Due to this limitation, it may be better to collapse the keyboard to a compact toolbar when an external keyboard is connected. You can always add a button that expands the keyboard again."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"ðŸ‘‘ Pro features","anchor":"ðŸ‘‘-Pro-features"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has an "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ExternalKeyboardContext","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" that can detect if an external keyboard is connected, including the Smart Keyboard Folio, Magic Keyboard, Bluetooth keyboards, etc.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To use this context, just set it up as an observed object:"}]},{"code":["struct CustomKeyboardView: View {","","   @StateObject","   var context = ExternalKeyboardContext()","","   var body: some View {","       VStack {","           Text(\"Is an external keyboard connected?\")","           Text(stateDescription)","       }.environmentObject(context)","   }","","   var stateDescription: String {","       context.isExternalKeyboardConnected.description","   }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the code above, we also inject the context into the view hierarchy as an environment object.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"warning","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The context considers a Apple Smart Keyboard Folio to be connected, even when itâ€™s just snapped on to the